es.eurohelp.lod.aldapa.core

Enum MethodRDFFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<MethodRDFFile>
      • es.eurohelp.lod.aldapa.core.MethodRDFFile
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<MethodRDFFile>

    public enum MethodRDFFile
extends Enum<MethodRDFFile>
    ALDAPA uses RDF to store information about execution and metadata about projects, datasets and the like. Since the templates storing the "backbone" RDF can be complex, they are codified in RDF in "Method files" that can be executed by ALDAPA by simply parametrising their inner tokens (PROJECT_NAME, ...) so that less code is written (hopefully). Also, that means that new RDF is not necessarily translated into more code.
    Author:
    Mikel Egana Aranguren, Eurohelp Consulting S.L.
